label: Thadrak Kanjur 'Dus 'khor 'grel pa sTod cha
description: The volumes contains the first volume of Kalacakra commentary composed by Pundarika. The name of the commentary is Vimalaprabhanamamulatantranusarinidvadashasahasrika-laghukalacakratantrarajatika. The volume is written on cream coloured traditional Bhutanese paper made from dahpne bark. It is written in black ink. The text is wrapped in several layers of cloth and bound between two think wood covers. The leaves are roughly 62x11.5cm. The first folios of the kanjur series have a deep blue background in the text box, most likely painted using malachite. Letters are written in gold ink. The text starts on the verso of the first folio which also has a silk cover. 1 volume containing 519 folios of manuscripts on paper in loose leaf poti format. Dates of original material: probably 18th century. Volume: sTod cha. Script(s) of material: Tibetan dBu can script.
